Well...

48
00:03:38,120 --> 00:03:40,440
- Give it time.
- <i>That's what I said, give it time.</i>

49
00:03:40,440 --> 00:03:42,360
Everyone would understand, but...

50
00:03:44,240 --> 00:03:47,520
he couldn't get back to school
and away from me quickly enough.

51
00:03:49,600 --> 00:03:51,560
<i>You said he likes his housemaster.</i>

52
00:03:51,560 --> 00:03:53,200
<i>Yes, Dr. Gailey.</i>

53
00:03:53,200 --> 00:03:54,680
<i>That's encouraging.</i>

54
00:03:54,680 --> 00:03:58,120
<i>I'm sure these days they've got better
at handling a situation like this.</i>

55
00:03:58,120 --> 00:04:02,160
<i>Oh, let's hope so. I'd hate it
for him to be at Gordonstoun in my day.</i>

56
00:04:02,680 --> 00:04:04,120
<i>Their idea of grief counseling</i>

57
00:04:04,120 --> 00:04:07,200
<i>would've been a cold shower
and a long march, cross-country.</i>

58
00:04:07,200 --> 00:04:08,400
What's wrong with that?

59
00:04:08,400 --> 00:04:11,720
Better than having some awful fuss made
and being mollycoddled.

60
00:04:11,720 --> 00:04:14,360
Yes. Well, we're different in that way.

61
00:04:14,360 --> 00:04:15,400
<i>Mmm.</i>

62
00:04:15,400 --> 00:04:17,160
<i>Does he have friends at school?</i>

63
